-- India cbank sets up panel to look into governance of boards of banks
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Mon Jan 20, 2014 04:56AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Jan 20 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India has set up a committee to look into the governance of boards of banks, it said on Monday.

The committee will analyse the representation in the bank boards, examine concentration risk, investigate possible conflicts of interest in board representation, including owner representatives and regulators, among other factors.